==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[fairground]] [[attraction]] in which participants ride through a [[haunted house]] in a [[railcar]].
# {{lb|en|theater}} An excursion done by many [[tourist]] [[railway]]s around the world. Usually, a [[fiction]]al story is created and performed with static displays or live actors on either side of a train. [[actor|Actor]]s and [[actress]]es play out a story on the long and narrow stage provided by the [[railcar]] [[aisle]]s.
# {{lb|en|UK}} A rail service which does not appear in the public timetables.
# {{lb|en|UK}} A supernatural manifestation of a railway locomotive or passenger cars.
# An unmanned train rolling on the train line.

